          },
          "faq_item_DBehzK": {
            "type": "faq_item",
            "settings": {
              "tab_id": "med-2",
              "question": "What does Nitric Oxide do for my body?",
              "answer": "<p>Nitric oxide boosts blood flow by relaxing and widening your blood vessels. That means more energy, better endurance, improved heart health — and even enhanced sexual performance. As we age, our body naturally produces less nitric oxide, so replenishing it can help you feel your best again.</p>",
              "open_by_default": false
            }
          },
          "faq_item_cPkQLg": {
            "type": "faq_item",
            "settings": {
              "tab_id": "med-2",
              "question": "How long do I need to take Berkeley Life before I see results?",
              "answer": "<p>Many customers feel the difference within days — more energy, better workouts, improved stamina. For others, it can take a few weeks. The good news? You don’t have to guess. Our Nitric Oxide Test Strips let you<em>see</em>the supplement working within just 90 minutes of taking it.</p>",
              "open_by_default": false
            }
          },
          "faq_item_f4diFA": {
            "type": "faq_item",
            "settings": {
              "tab_id": "med-2",
              "question": "Can I take Berkeley Life with other medications?",
              "answer": "<p>Yes. Berkeley Life is safe, well-tolerated, and has no known interactions with medications. Still, if you're on a specific treatment plan, it's always smart to check with your doctor.</p>",
              "open_by_default": false
            }
          },
          "faq_item_mP4MrQ": {
            "type": "faq_item",
            "settings": {
              "tab_id": "med-2",
              "question": "Is this product safe? Are there any side effects?",
              "answer": "<p>Yes, Berkeley Life’s Nitric Oxide Foundation is clinically tested and drug-free. It’s generally well-tolerated, but as with any supplement, consult your healthcare provider if you have concerns.</p>",
              "open_by_default": false
            }
          },
          "faq_item_T3xTaK": {
            "type": "faq_item",
            "settings": {
              "tab_id": "med-2",
              "question": "Can I get the dietary nitrates in Berkeley Life just through my diet?",
              "answer": "<p>Leafy greens, beetroot, arugula, spinach and celery are all vegetables known to be high in dietary nitrates. However, nutrient density of the soil across the country makes it difficult to predict exactly how much of these greens are required daily to provide a clinically effective dose of nitrates to produce nitric oxide. In our experience, it requires more leafy greens than most people over 35 are willing or able to consume every day.</p>",
              "open_by_default": false
            }
          }
        },
